HEADWORD: zaman
<hw>za"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
large ornamental tropical American tree (<spn>Albizia saman</spn>) with
bipinnate leaves and globose clusters of flowers with crimson stamens
and sweet-pulp seed pods eaten by cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rain tree, saman, monkeypod, monkey pod,
zamang.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

